-- Hong Kong benchmark slips, led down by Tencent
-- By Natalie Thomas
-- Thu Mar 27, 2014 04:16AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, March 27 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares fell on Wednesday as investors staged a sell-off of index tech heavyweight Tencent Holdings after U.S-listed peers declined.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> ended down 0.3 percent at 21,834.5, though the China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the top Chinese listings in Hong Kong rose 0.2 percent. Shares in Internet giant Tencent <0700.HK> fell 6.3 percent after the company announced it was buying a 28 percent stake in South Korean mobile gaming firm CJ Games for $500 million.